Functional Requirements
1. view list of problems
2. view a problem detail
3. submit solution
4. view leader board

non functional Requirement
1. highly availability, eventual consistency
2. isolation while running code
3. return submission result in 5 seconds
4. competition with 100k users

entities
1. Problem-This entity will store the problem statement, test cases, and the expected output.
2. Submission-This entity will store the user's code submission and the result of running the code against the test cases.
3. Leaderboard-This entity will store the leaderboard for competitions.

API
GET /problems?page=1&limit=10 -> List<Problem>
GET /problems/{id}?language={language} -> Problem with code stub in that specific language
POST /problems/{id}/submit -> Submission
{
   code:string,
   language:string
}
GET /leaderboard/:competitionId?page=1&limit=100 -> Leaderboard

